OL,3,C'Five basic failures' at hospital
OL,4,Cwhere Lucy Letby worked, inquiry told
OL,6,FBasic failures by the hospital where
OL,7,Fkiller nurse Lucy Letby worked had
OL,8,F"fatal consequences" for babies, an
OL,9,Finquiry into her crimes has heard.
OL,11,FOn the third day of the Thirlwall
OL,12,FInquiry in Liverpool, an opening
OL,13,Fstatement was given by Peter Skelton
OL,14,FKC, representing seven of the families.
OL,16,FThe inquiry was set up to examine how
OL,17,Fthe 34-year-old nurse was able to
OL,18,Fcarry out her crimes in the neonatal
OL,19,Funit of the Countess of Chester
OL,20,FHospital in 2015 and 2016.
